{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":800,"text":"There are times when I feel\nreally quite ashamed"},{"time":4280,"text":"to be a European."},{"time":6200,"text":"In the last year,"},{"time":8080,"text":"more than a million people\narrived in Europe in need of our help,"},{"time":12680,"text":"and our response,\nfrankly, has been pathetic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":17000,"text":"There are just so many contradictions."},{"time":20360,"text":"We mourn the tragic death"},{"time":22840,"text":"of two-year-old Alan Kurdi,"},{"time":26000,"text":"and yet, since then,\nmore than 200 children"},{"time":29880,"text":"have subsequently drowned\nin the Mediterranean."},{"time":33960,"text":"We have international treaties"},{"time":35440,"text":"that recognize that refugees\nare a shared responsibility,"},{"time":38680,"text":"and yet we accept that tiny Lebanon"},{"time":41760,"text":"hosts more Syrians\nthan the whole of Europe combined."},{"time":46320,"text":"We lament the existence\nof human smugglers,"},{"time":50360,"text":"and yet we make that the only viable route"},{"time":53800,"text":"to seek asylum in Europe."},{"time":56840,"text":"We have labor shortages,"},{"time":58720,"text":"and yet we exclude people who fit\nour economic and demographic needs"},{"time":64200,"text":"from coming to Europe."},{"time":67000,"text":"We proclaim our liberal values\nin opposition to fundamentalist Islam,"},{"time":72960,"text":"and yet --"},{"time":75560,"text":"we have repressive policies"},{"time":78240,"text":"that detain child asylum seekers,"},{"time":81160,"text":"that separate children\nfrom their families,"},{"time":84800,"text":"and that seize property from refugees."}]},{"cues":[{"time":88960,"text":"What are we doing?"},{"time":90640,"text":"How has the situation come to this,"},{"time":93080,"text":"that we've adopted such an inhumane\nresponse to a humanitarian crisis?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":99280,"text":"I don't believe\nit's because people don't care,"},{"time":101720,"text":"or at least I don't want to believe\nit's because people don't care."},{"time":104920,"text":"I believe it's because\nour politicians lack a vision,"},{"time":108760,"text":"a vision for how to adapt\nan international refugee system"},{"time":112400,"text":"created over 50 years ago"},{"time":114560,"text":"for a changing and globalized world."},{"time":117800,"text":"And so what I want to do\nis take a step back"},{"time":120360,"text":"and ask two really fundamental questions,"},{"time":123800,"text":"the two questions we all need to ask."},{"time":126280,"text":"First, why is the current\nsystem not working?"},{"time":129600,"text":"And second, what can we do to fix it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":134760,"text":"So the modern refugee regime"},{"time":136840,"text":"was created in the aftermath\nof the Second World War by these guys."},{"time":142000,"text":"Its basic aim is to ensure"},{"time":145160,"text":"that when a state fails,\nor worse, turns against its own people,"},{"time":149400,"text":"people have somewhere to go,"},{"time":151000,"text":"to live in safety and dignity\nuntil they can go home."},{"time":154680,"text":"It was created precisely for situations\nlike the situation we see in Syria today."},{"time":160680,"text":"Through an international convention\nsigned by 147 governments,"},{"time":165560,"text":"the 1951 Convention\non the Status of Refugees,"},{"time":168600,"text":"and an international organization, UNHCR,"},{"time":171800,"text":"states committed to reciprocally\nadmit people onto their territory"},{"time":176600,"text":"who flee conflict and persecution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":179680,"text":"But today, that system is failing."},{"time":182920,"text":"In theory, refugees\nhave a right to seek asylum."},{"time":186880,"text":"In practice, our immigration policies\nblock the path to safety."},{"time":191280,"text":"In theory, refugees have a right\nto a pathway to integration,"},{"time":195640,"text":"or return to the country\nthey've come from."},{"time":198360,"text":"But in practice, they get stuck\nin almost indefinite limbo."},{"time":202240,"text":"In theory, refugees\nare a shared global responsibility."},{"time":206040,"text":"In practice, geography means\nthat countries proximate the conflict"},{"time":210400,"text":"take the overwhelming majority\nof the world's refugees."},{"time":214720,"text":"The system isn't broken\nbecause the rules are wrong."},{"time":217480,"text":"It's that we're not applying them\nadequately to a changing world,"},{"time":221840,"text":"and that's what we need to reconsider."}]},{"cues":[{"time":224440,"text":"So I want to explain to you a little bit\nabout how the current system works."},{"time":228960,"text":"How does the refugee regime actually work?"},{"time":231560,"text":"But not from a top-down\ninstitutional perspective,"},{"time":234360,"text":"rather from the perspective of a refugee."},{"time":238240,"text":"So imagine a Syrian woman."},{"time":240720,"text":"Let's call her Amira."},{"time":242880,"text":"And Amira to me represents\nmany of the people I've met in the region."},{"time":247560,"text":"Amira, like around 25 percent\nof the world's refugees,"},{"time":250920,"text":"is a woman with children,"},{"time":252840,"text":"and she can't go home\nbecause she comes from this city"},{"time":256120,"text":"that you see before you, Homs,"},{"time":258160,"text":"a once beautiful and historic city"},{"time":260920,"text":"now under rubble."},{"time":262440,"text":"And so Amira can't go back there."},{"time":265120,"text":"But Amira also has no hope\nof resettlement to a third country,"},{"time":269360,"text":"because that's a lottery ticket"},{"time":270880,"text":"only available to less than one percent\nof the world's refugees."}]},{"cues":[{"time":274880,"text":"So Amira and her family"},{"time":277160,"text":"face an almost impossible choice."},{"time":279360,"text":"They have three basic options."},{"time":282560,"text":"The first option is that Amira\ncan take her family to a camp."},{"time":288520,"text":"In the camp, she might get assistance,"},{"time":291160,"text":"but there are very few prospects\nfor Amira and her family."},{"time":294880,"text":"Camps are in bleak, arid locations,"},{"time":298160,"text":"often in the desert."},{"time":300040,"text":"In the Zaatari refugee camp in Jordan,"},{"time":302760,"text":"you can hear the shells\nacross the border in Syria at nighttime."},{"time":308600,"text":"There's restricted economic activity."},{"time":311200,"text":"Education is often of poor quality."},{"time":313960,"text":"And around the world,"},{"time":315320,"text":"some 80 percent of refugees\nwho are in camps"},{"time":318440,"text":"have to stay for at least five years."},{"time":321000,"text":"It's a miserable existence,"},{"time":322920,"text":"and that's probably why, in reality,"},{"time":325320,"text":"only nine percent of Syrians\nchoose that option."}]},{"cues":[{"time":329000,"text":"Alternatively, Amira can head\nto an urban area"},{"time":333000,"text":"in a neighboring country,\nlike Amman or Beirut."},{"time":337000,"text":"That's an option that about 75 percent\nof Syrian refugees have taken."},{"time":342200,"text":"But there, there's\ngreat difficulty as well."},{"time":345720,"text":"Refugees in such urban areas\ndon't usually have the right to work."},{"time":350040,"text":"They don't usually get\nsignificant access to assistance."},{"time":353440,"text":"And so when Amira and her family\nhave used up their basic savings,"},{"time":357160,"text":"they're left with very little\nand likely to face urban destitution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":362280,"text":"So there's a third alternative,"},{"time":364920,"text":"and it's one that increasing\nnumbers of Syrians are taking."},{"time":369840,"text":"Amira can seek some hope for her family"},{"time":374040,"text":"by risking their lives\non a dangerous and perilous journey"},{"time":377800,"text":"to another country,"},{"time":379320,"text":"and it's that which we're seeing\nin Europe today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":383440,"text":"Around the world, we present refugees\nwith an almost impossible choice"},{"time":388720,"text":"between three options:"},{"time":390560,"text":"encampment, urban destitution\nand dangerous journeys."},{"time":395520,"text":"For refugees, that choice is\nthe global refugee regime today."},{"time":400600,"text":"But I think it's a false choice."},{"time":402760,"text":"I think we can reconsider that choice."},{"time":405440,"text":"The reason why we limit those options"},{"time":410040,"text":"is because we think"},{"time":413080,"text":"that those are the only options\nthat are available to refugees,"},{"time":417480,"text":"and they're not."},{"time":419120,"text":"Politicians frame the issue\nas a zero-sum issue,"},{"time":422640,"text":"that if we benefit refugees,\nwe're imposing costs on citizens."},{"time":426600,"text":"We tend to have a collective assumption"},{"time":428680,"text":"that refugees are an inevitable cost\nor burden to society."},{"time":432360,"text":"But they don't have to.\nThey can contribute."}]},{"cues":[{"time":434880,"text":"So what I want to argue"},{"time":436320,"text":"is there are ways in which we can\nexpand that choice set"},{"time":439320,"text":"and still benefit everyone else:"},{"time":441360,"text":"the host states and communities,"},{"time":443240,"text":"our societies and refugees themselves."},{"time":447080,"text":"And I want to suggest four ways"},{"time":449080,"text":"we can transform the paradigm\nof how we think about refugees."},{"time":453520,"text":"All four ways have one thing in common:"},{"time":456440,"text":"they're all ways in which we take\nthe opportunities of globalization,"},{"time":460240,"text":"mobility and markets,"},{"time":462320,"text":"and update the way we think\nabout the refugee issue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":466280,"text":"The first one I want to think about"},{"time":468000,"text":"is the idea of enabling environments,"},{"time":470720,"text":"and it starts from\na very basic recognition"},{"time":473600,"text":"that refugees are human beings\nlike everyone else,"},{"time":476320,"text":"but they're just\nin extraordinary circumstances."},{"time":479280,"text":"Together with my colleagues in Oxford,"},{"time":481280,"text":"we've embarked on\na research project in Uganda"},{"time":483960,"text":"looking at the economic lives of refugees."},{"time":487840,"text":"We chose Uganda not because\nit's representative of all host countries."},{"time":491920,"text":"It's not. It's exceptional."},{"time":493960,"text":"Unlike most host countries\naround the world,"},{"time":496360,"text":"what Uganda has done"},{"time":497840,"text":"is give refugees economic opportunity."},{"time":500240,"text":"It gives them the right to work.\nIt gives them freedom of movement."},{"time":504200,"text":"And the results of that are extraordinary"},{"time":507120,"text":"both for refugees and the host community."},{"time":510480,"text":"In the capital city, Kampala,"},{"time":512480,"text":"we found that 21 percent of refugees\nown a business that employs other people,"},{"time":517919,"text":"and 40 percent of those employees"},{"time":520400,"text":"are nationals of the host country."},{"time":522400,"text":"In other words, refugees are making jobs"},{"time":524600,"text":"for citizens of the host country."},{"time":527920,"text":"Even in the camps,\nwe found extraordinary examples"},{"time":531280,"text":"of vibrant, flourishing\nand entrepreneurial businesses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":535800,"text":"For example, in a settlement\ncalled Nakivale,"},{"time":539160,"text":"we found examples of Congolese refugees"},{"time":542160,"text":"running digital music exchange businesses."},{"time":544720,"text":"We found a Rwandan\nwho runs a business that's available"},{"time":548520,"text":"to allow the youth to play computer games"},{"time":551280,"text":"on recycled games consoles\nand recycled televisions."},{"time":556440,"text":"Against the odds of extreme constraint,"},{"time":559280,"text":"refugees are innovating,"},{"time":561320,"text":"and the gentleman you see before you\nis a Congolese guy called Demou-Kay."},{"time":565200,"text":"Demou-Kay arrived\nin the settlement with very little,"},{"time":568880,"text":"but he wanted to be a filmmaker."},{"time":571200,"text":"So with friends and colleagues,\nhe started a community radio station,"},{"time":575160,"text":"he rented a video camera,"},{"time":576920,"text":"and he's now making films."},{"time":578440,"text":"He made two documentary films"},{"time":580440,"text":"with and for our team,"},{"time":582440,"text":"and he's making a successful business\nout of very little."},{"time":586640,"text":"It's those kinds of examples"},{"time":588640,"text":"that should guide\nour response to refugees."},{"time":591400,"text":"Rather than seeing refugees"},{"time":592760,"text":"as inevitably dependent\nupon humanitarian assistance,"},{"time":596040,"text":"we need to provide them\nwith opportunities for human flourishing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":600200,"text":"Yes, clothes, blankets, shelter, food"},{"time":604438,"text":"are all important in the emergency phase,"},{"time":607240,"text":"but we need to also look beyond that."},{"time":610200,"text":"We need to provide opportunities\nto connectivity, electricity,"},{"time":614560,"text":"education, the right to work,"},{"time":617400,"text":"access to capital and banking."},{"time":619560,"text":"All the ways in which we take for granted"},{"time":621720,"text":"that we are plugged in\nto the global economy"},{"time":623880,"text":"can and should apply to refugees."}]},{"cues":[{"time":627280,"text":"The second idea I want to discuss\nis economic zones."},{"time":631320,"text":"Unfortunately, not every\nhost country in the world"},{"time":634080,"text":"takes the approach Uganda has taken."},{"time":636480,"text":"Most host countries don't open up\ntheir economies to refugees"},{"time":639840,"text":"in the same way."},{"time":641360,"text":"But there are still pragmatic\nalternative options that we can use."}]},{"cues":[{"time":647160,"text":"Last April, I traveled to Jordan\nwith my colleague,"},{"time":649720,"text":"the development economist Paul Collier,"},{"time":652400,"text":"and we brainstormed an idea\nwhile we were there"},{"time":655280,"text":"with the international community\nand the government,"},{"time":657760,"text":"an idea to bring jobs to Syrians"},{"time":660120,"text":"while supporting Jordan's\nnational development strategy."},{"time":663760,"text":"The idea is for an economic zone,"},{"time":667080,"text":"one in which we could potentially\nintegrate the employment of refugees"},{"time":670640,"text":"alongside the employment\nof Jordanian host nationals."},{"time":674840,"text":"And just 15 minutes away\nfrom the Zaatari refugee camp,"},{"time":678280,"text":"home to 83,000 refugees,"},{"time":680440,"text":"is an existing economic zone"},{"time":682480,"text":"called the King Hussein\nBin Talal Development Area."},{"time":685920,"text":"The government has spent\nover a hundred million dollars"},{"time":688720,"text":"connecting it to the electricity grid,\nconnecting it to the road network,"},{"time":692560,"text":"but it lacked two things:"},{"time":694200,"text":"access to labor and inward investment."},{"time":696960,"text":"So what if refugees\nwere able to work there"},{"time":699880,"text":"rather than being stuck in camps,"},{"time":701720,"text":"able to support their families and develop\nskills through vocational training"},{"time":705760,"text":"before they go back to Syria?"},{"time":707840,"text":"We recognized that\nthat could benefit Jordan,"},{"time":710160,"text":"whose development strategy\nrequires it to make the leap"},{"time":712960,"text":"as a middle income country\nto manufacturing."},{"time":715800,"text":"It could benefit refugees,\nbut it could also contribute"},{"time":719520,"text":"to the postconflict\nreconstruction of Syria"},{"time":721920,"text":"by recognizing that we need\nto incubate refugees"},{"time":724720,"text":"as the best source\nof eventually rebuilding Syria."}]},{"cues":[{"time":728760,"text":"We published the idea\nin the journal Foreign Affairs."},{"time":731840,"text":"King Abdullah has picked up on the idea."},{"time":734080,"text":"It was announced at the London\nSyria Conference two weeks ago,"},{"time":737080,"text":"and a pilot will begin in the summer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":740120,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":745120,"text":"The third idea that I want to put to you"},{"time":747840,"text":"is preference matching\nbetween states and refugees"},{"time":751480,"text":"to lead to the kinds of happy outcomes\nyou see here in the selfie"},{"time":754640,"text":"featuring Angela Merkel\nand a Syrian refugee."},{"time":758440,"text":"What we rarely do is ask refugees\nwhat they want, where they want to go,"},{"time":762960,"text":"but I'd argue we can do that"},{"time":764840,"text":"and still make everyone better off."},{"time":767640,"text":"The economist Alvin Roth has developed\nthe idea of matching markets,"},{"time":771800,"text":"ways in which the preference ranking\nof the parties shapes an eventual match."},{"time":777720,"text":"My colleagues Will Jones\nand Alex Teytelboym"},{"time":780800,"text":"have explored ways in which that idea\ncould be applied to refugees,"},{"time":784960,"text":"to ask refugees to rank\ntheir preferred destinations,"},{"time":788520,"text":"but also allow states to rank\nthe types of refugees they want"},{"time":792320,"text":"on skills criteria or language criteria"},{"time":795160,"text":"and allow those to match."},{"time":796880,"text":"Now, of course\nyou'd need to build in quotas"},{"time":799000,"text":"on things like diversity\nand vulnerability,"},{"time":802280,"text":"but it's a way of increasing\nthe possibilities of matching."},{"time":805840,"text":"The matching idea\nhas been successfully used"},{"time":808360,"text":"to match, for instance,\nstudents with university places,"},{"time":813520,"text":"to match kidney donors with patients,"},{"time":816040,"text":"and it underlies the kind of algorithms\nthat exist on dating websites."},{"time":820200,"text":"So why not apply that\nto give refugees greater choice?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":823320,"text":"It could also be used\nat the national level,"},{"time":825392,"text":"where one of the great challenges we face"},{"time":827400,"text":"is to persuade local communities\nto accept refugees."},{"time":831160,"text":"And at the moment,\nin my country, for instance,"},{"time":833640,"text":"we often send engineers to rural areas\nand farmers to the cities,"},{"time":837840,"text":"which makes no sense at all."},{"time":839720,"text":"So matching markets offer a potential way\nto bring those preferences together"},{"time":844320,"text":"and listen to the needs and demands\nof the populations that host"},{"time":848280,"text":"and the refugees themselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":850840,"text":"The fourth idea I want to put to you\nis of humanitarian visas."},{"time":855240,"text":"Much of the tragedy and chaos\nwe've seen in Europe"},{"time":857960,"text":"was entirely avoidable."},{"time":860400,"text":"It stems from a fundamental contradiction\nin Europe's asylum policy,"},{"time":864520,"text":"which is the following:"},{"time":865920,"text":"that in order to seek asylum in Europe,"},{"time":868440,"text":"you have to arrive spontaneously\nby embarking on those dangerous journeys"},{"time":873480,"text":"that I described."},{"time":875520,"text":"But why should those journeys be necessary\nin an era of the budget airline"},{"time":880280,"text":"and modern consular capabilities?"},{"time":882720,"text":"They're completely unnecessary journeys,"},{"time":885080,"text":"and last year, they led to the deaths\nof over 3,000 people"},{"time":888880,"text":"on Europe's borders\nand within European territory."}]},{"cues":[{"time":893360,"text":"If refugees were simply allowed"},{"time":895000,"text":"to travel directly\nand seek asylum in Europe,"},{"time":897800,"text":"we would avoid that,"},{"time":899120,"text":"and there's a way of doing that"},{"time":900680,"text":"through something\ncalled a humanitarian visa,"},{"time":903000,"text":"that allows people\nto collect a visa at an embassy"},{"time":906560,"text":"or a consulate in a neighboring country"},{"time":908720,"text":"and then simply pay their own way"},{"time":910640,"text":"through a ferry or a flight to Europe."},{"time":914000,"text":"It costs around a thousand euros"},{"time":916000,"text":"to take a smuggler\nfrom Turkey to the Greek islands."},{"time":919440,"text":"It costs 200 euros to take a budget\nairline from Bodrum to Frankfurt."},{"time":924920,"text":"If we allowed refugees to do that,\nit would have major advantages."},{"time":928720,"text":"It would save lives,"},{"time":930760,"text":"it would undercut\nthe entire market for smugglers,"},{"time":934720,"text":"and it would remove the chaos\nwe see from Europe's front line"},{"time":938080,"text":"in areas like the Greek islands."},{"time":940160,"text":"It's politics that prevents us doing that\nrather than a rational solution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":944880,"text":"And this is an idea that has been applied."},{"time":947240,"text":"Brazil has adopted a pioneering approach"},{"time":949920,"text":"where over 2,000 Syrians\nhave been able to get humanitarian visas,"},{"time":954240,"text":"enter Brazil, and claim refugee status\non arrival in Brazil."},{"time":958640,"text":"And in that scheme,\nevery Syrian who has gone through it"},{"time":961560,"text":"has received refugee status\nand been recognized as a genuine refugee."}]},{"cues":[{"time":966160,"text":"There is a historical precedent\nfor it as well."},{"time":968920,"text":"Between 1922 and 1942,"},{"time":972280,"text":"these Nansen passports\nwere used as travel documents"},{"time":976080,"text":"to allow 450,000 Assyrians,\nTurks and Chechens"},{"time":981640,"text":"to travel across Europe"},{"time":983160,"text":"and claim refugee status\nelsewhere in Europe."},{"time":986520,"text":"And the Nansen\nInternational Refugee Office"},{"time":989280,"text":"received the Nobel Peace Prize"},{"time":991160,"text":"in recognition of this\nbeing a viable strategy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":995000,"text":"So all four of these ideas\nthat I've presented you"},{"time":998240,"text":"are ways in which we can expand\nAmira's choice set."},{"time":1001920,"text":"They're ways in which we can have\ngreater choice for refugees"},{"time":1005200,"text":"beyond those basic,\nimpossible three options"},{"time":1009040,"text":"I explained to you"},{"time":1010280,"text":"and still leave others better off."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1012960,"text":"In conclusion,\nwe really need a new vision,"},{"time":1016360,"text":"a vision that enlarges\nthe choices of refugees"},{"time":1019160,"text":"but recognizes that they\ndon't have to be a burden."},{"time":1021720,"text":"There's nothing inevitable\nabout refugees being a cost."},{"time":1025200,"text":"Yes, they are a humanitarian\nresponsibility,"},{"time":1028480,"text":"but they're human beings\nwith skills, talents, aspirations,"},{"time":1032119,"text":"with the ability to make\ncontributions -- if we let them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1036520,"text":"In the new world,"},{"time":1038319,"text":"migration is not going to go away."},{"time":1040599,"text":"What we've seen in Europe\nwill be with us for many years."},{"time":1043599,"text":"People will continue to travel,"},{"time":1045440,"text":"they'll continue to be displaced,"},{"time":1047319,"text":"and we need to find rational,\nrealistic ways of managing this --"},{"time":1050840,"text":"not based on the old logics\nof humanitarian assistance,"},{"time":1053880,"text":"not based on logics of charity,"},{"time":1056000,"text":"but building on the opportunities"},{"time":1057640,"text":"offered by globalization,\nmarkets and mobility."},{"time":1061040,"text":"I'd urge you all to wake up\nand urge our politicians"},{"time":1064480,"text":"to wake up to this challenge."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1066360,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1067640,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}